The paper discusses the mechanism of deep learning and the efficient representations extracted from data, which are topics closely related to machine learning and artificial intelligence. Therefore, cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also discusses the cost of representing inputs and the entropy of frequency of states, which are related to information theory, suggesting cs.IT (Information Theory) as another likely sub-category. Additionally, the paper discusses the hierarchy of representations and the power law distributions, which are related to complex systems and statistical physics, suggesting cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) as a possible sub-category.
